<paragraph id="8B83A42D9C284B6309AAAE00FDA1FA61" blockId="15.[156,772,883,1426]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDFAE9C284B6309AAAE00FD7AFBD2" authority="Kaszab 1976: 187" authorityName="Kaszab" authorityPageNumber="187" authorityYear="1976" box="[156,767,1036,1058]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Stomion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="galapagoensis" subSpecies="leleupi">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B6309AAAE00FD8EFBD2" box="[156,523,1036,1057]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Stomion galapagoensis leleupi</emphasis>
Kaszab 1976: 187
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="54871A8F9C284B630982AE27FE9FFBB2" box="[180,282,1067,1089]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Holotype</typeStatus>
male and 
<specimenCount id="9D3A6FA49C284B6308A9AE27FDBDFBB3" box="[415,568,1067,1088]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
in KBIN (examined). Type locality: Santa Cruz. Label data: under stones in crater at island summit [Cerro Crocker], locality G 35, 
<date id="FF8282ED9C284B630852AE8BFD86FB6E" box="[356,515,1159,1181]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" value="1965-02-12" valueMax="1965-02-17" valueMin="1965-02-12">12–17.II.1965</date>
, leg. J. &amp; N. Leleup. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFADD9DC9C284B630982AEAAFEEBFB49" author="Franz H" box="[180,366,1189,1211]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" pagination="73 - 124" refId="ref11536" refString="Franz H. 1985. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Koleopterenfauna der Galapagos-Inseln. Situngsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Abteilung 194: 73 - 124." type="journal article" year="1985">Franz 1985: 92</bibRefCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B630849AEA9FDC2FB49" bold="true" box="[383,583,1189,1210]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">New synonymy</emphasis>
. Notes. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFADD9DC9C284B630B86AEA9FEB7FB29" author="Kaszab Z" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" pagination="183 - 210" refId="ref12004" refString="Kaszab Z. 1970. XIII. Coleoptera Tenebrionidae. Mission Zoologique Belge Aux Iles Galapagos et En Ecuador (N et Journal of Leleup, 1964 - 1965) 2: 183 - 210." type="journal article" year="1970">Kaszab (1970: 188)</bibRefCitation>
states that his 
<specimenCount id="9D3A6FA49C284B6308D4AEC8FDC6FB2A" box="[482,579,1220,1241]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" type="generic">two type</specimenCount>
specimens could not be distinguished from specimens supposedly collected by J. &amp; N. Leleup in an unspecified locality in continental 
<collectingCountry id="F32BE4BD9C284B630809AF2CFE1AFAC5" box="[319,415,1312,1334]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. We agree that they cannot be separated and must conclude that they represent another case of mislabelling, and that 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDFAE9C284B630B5DAF52FD4FFA81" box="[619,714,1373,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Stomion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linelli">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B630B5DAF52FD4FFA81" box="[619,714,1373,1395]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">S. linelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not occur on mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F32BE4BD9C284B630889AF70FDA5FA61" box="[447,544,1404,1426]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C326F7A69C284B6309AAAFA7FC35FE0F" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B83A42D9C284B6309AAAFA7FE91F900" blockId="15.[156,771,1450,1779]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B6309AAAFA7FE96FA33" box="[156,275,1451,1472]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CC409C89C284B6308B1AFA6FE60FA4C" box="[391,485,1450,1471]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CC409C89C284B630B60AFA6FD31FA4C" box="[598,692,1450,1472]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
; body broad, &lt;2.0¥ longer than wide; overall body surface smooth; fine, sparse punctures on pronotum and elytra; pronotum apical margin nearly straight; pronotum transverse, 1.7¥ wider than long, noticeably narrow at apex and broadening continually toward the base; elytra smooth with punctures very fine, sometimes obsolete, arranged in parallel rows; abdomen broad and convex, giving a robust shape; dorsal tooth of right mandible present, well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A42D9C284B6309AAAD07FBDDFEE5" blockId="15.[156,772,1803,1886]" lastBlockId="15.[820,1436,195,278]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B6309AAAD07FEA8F8D3" box="[156,301,1803,1824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Distribution:</emphasis>
Widespread as the nominate subspecies (
<figureCitation id="1307B8A89C284B630995AD25FEA3F8B3" box="[163,294,1833,1856]" captionStart="Figures 30–35" captionStartId="13.[156,246,1064,1083]" captionTargetBox="[182,1406,198,1031]" captionTargetId="figure-394@13.[182,1408,198,1032]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 30–35. Scanning electron micrographs of the head and pronotum (18¥), with inset of pronotal disc (300¥) and the elytral disc (100¥). Figs 30, 31. S. laevigatum; Figs 32, 33. S. linelli linelli; Figs 34, 35. S. linelli leleupi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5429644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5429644/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Figs 32, 33</figureCitation>
) on Baltra, Bartolomé, Beagle, Daphne Major, Eden, Rabida, Santiago, Seymour and South Plazas islands, and as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDFAE9C284B630D01AACFFB6FFF2B" box="[1079,1258,195,216]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Stomion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="linelli" subSpecies="leleupi">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B630D01AACFFB6FFF2B" box="[1079,1258,195,216]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">S. linelli leleupi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1307B8A89C284B630DCFAACFFAF3FF2A" box="[1273,1398,195,217]" captionStart="Figures 30–35" captionStartId="13.[156,246,1064,1083]" captionTargetBox="[182,1406,198,1031]" captionTargetId="figure-394@13.[182,1408,198,1032]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 30–35. Scanning electron micrographs of the head and pronotum (18¥), with inset of pronotal disc (300¥) and the elytral disc (100¥). Figs 30, 31. S. laevigatum; Figs 32, 33. S. linelli linelli; Figs 34, 35. S. linelli leleupi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5429644" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5429644/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Figs 34, 35</figureCitation>
) in the uplands and north slope of Santa Cruz Island. Not 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDFAE9C284B630A02AB0CFB85FEE5" authority="(Tower)" baseAuthorityName="Tower" box="[820,1024,256,278]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Stomion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genovesa">Genovesa (Tower)</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F32BE4BD9C284B630D3FAB0CFBD1FEE5" box="[1033,1108,256,278]" name="Iceland" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Island</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A42D9C284B630A02AB23FC35FE0F" blockId="15.[820,1435,302,508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis id="B948783F9C284B630A02AB23FC35FEB7" box="[820,944,303,324]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="150">Bionomics:</emphasis>
The species occurs in the littoral and arid zones, on coastal dunes and in mangrove debris and shrub litter and at carrion from sea level to upper transition zone forests at 
<quantity id="4CC409C89C284B630D60AB86FB18FE53" box="[1110,1181,394,416]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
elevation, on both ash and soil substrates. Adults collected in January, March to July, and November. Examined: 
<specimenCount id="9D3A6FA49C284B630C44ABCBFC28FE0F" pageId="15" pageNumber="150" type="generic">571 specimens</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
